        "timestamp": "2018-03-13 22:14:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nW have to install GNU autotools on jenkins job server, do we need to be root to install?\nI move the installation commands to our project script",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "36fab10d1abe2172b851b4eb66ba6f6121765f8a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-13 23:01:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe Jenkins nodes do accept sudo commands in case you need to. If you want to install a specific version for these, I don't think you need sudo permissions though as far as I can tell from https://askubuntu.com/questions/430706/installing-autotools-autoconf\n\nYou can always test any installation in the Jenkins Sandbox for verification, but \"sudo apt-get install autotools-dev\" for example should work..https://jenkins.onap.org/sandbox/job/test/5/",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
